{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.19",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 19 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:2",
      "text": "How long will ye vex my soul, and destroy me with words? only know that the Lord has dealt with me thus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:3",
      "text": "Ye speak against me; ye do not feel for me, but bear hard upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:4",
      "text": "Yea verily, I have erred in truth, (but the error abides with myself) Job 19:4a 4a in having spoken words which it was not right to speak; and my words err, and are unseasonable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:5",
      "text": "But alas! for ye magnify yourselves against me, and insult me with reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:6",
      "text": "Know then that it is the Lord that has troubled me, and has raised his bulwark against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:7",
      "text": "Behold, I laugh at reproach; I will not speak: or I will cry out, but there is nowhere judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:8",
      "text": "I am fenced round about, and can by no means escape: he has set darkness before my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:9",
      "text": "And he has stripped me of my glory, and has taken the crown from my head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:10",
      "text": "He has torn me round about, and I am gone: and he has cut off my hope like a tree.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:11",
      "text": "And he has dreadfully handled me in anger, and has counted me for an enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:12",
      "text": "His troops also came upon me with one accord, liers in wait compassed my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:13",
      "text": "My brethren have stood aloof from me; they have recognised strangers rather than me: and my friends have become pitiless.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:14",
      "text": "My nearest of kin have not acknowledged me, and they that knew my name, have forgotten me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:15",
      "text": "As for my household, and my maid-servants, I was a stranger before them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:16",
      "text": "I called my servant, and he hearkened not; and my mouth intreated him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:17",
      "text": "And I besought my wife, and earnestly intreated the sons of my concubines.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:18",
      "text": "But they rejected me for ever; whenever I rise up, they speak against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:19",
      "text": "They that saw me abhorred me: the very persons whom I had loved, rose up against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:20",
      "text": "My flesh is corrupt under my skin, and my bones are held in my teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:21",
      "text": "Pity me, pity me, O friends; for it is the hand of the Lord that has touched me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:22",
      "text": "Wherefore do ye persecute me as also the Lord does, and are not satisfied with my flesh?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:23",
      "text": "For oh that my words were written, and that they were recorded in a book for ever,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:24",
      "text": "with an iron pen and lead, or graven in the rocks!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:25",
      "text": "For I know that he is eternal who is about to deliver me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:26",
      "text": "and to raise up upon the earth my skin that endures these sufferings: for these things have been accomplished to me of the Lord;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:27",
      "text": "which I am conscious of in myself, which mine eye has seen, and not another, but all have been fulfilled to me in my bosom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:28",
      "text": "But if ye shall also say, What shall we say before him, and so find the root of the matter in him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.19.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:29",
      "text": "Do ye also beware of deceit: for wrath will come upon transgressors; and then shall they know where their substance is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
